cs.HC, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on studying film-maker's working practices and proposing a new quadrotor camera tool that brings expert workflows closer to end-users. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper discusses the design of a quadrotor camera tool and proposes extensions to an existing algorithm for generating camera motions. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of a camera in aerial videography. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is relevant as the paper discusses the design of a tool for creating complex aerial video shots. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of a camera in creating videos.
